er\n59: - Tabs/sections: Overview, Facts & Features, Schools, Nearby\n60: - Description (free text)\n61: - Amenities list with icons\n62: - Google Map embed with pin\n63: - Sidebar: Request Tour / Apply / Contact buttons\n64: - Favorite toggle (heart icon)\n65: \n66: **Renter Hub (Dashboard):**\n67: - Sidebar nav: Search, Saved Searches, Favorites, Messages, Applications, Payments\n68: - Central dashboard showing recent activity, application statuses\n69: - \"Your search\" section: active searches with new listing counts\n70: \n71: **Mobile Bottom Nav (Zillow homepage):**\n72: - Search | Updates | Favorites | Home Loans | Inbox\n73: - 5-tab pattern; Favorites and Updates keep users returning\n74: \n75: **Zillow Group Ecosystem (subsidiaries):**\n76: - Trulia (trulia.com), StreetEasy (streeteasy.com), HotPads (hotpads.com), Out East (outeast.com)\n77: - All share design DNA (card-based listings, map integration), adapted for regional/demographic needs\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ### Competitor 2: Apartments.com\n82: \n83: **Type:** Rental aggregator with heavy advertising model\n84: **USP:** Massive inventory, neighborhood guides, 3D tours\n85: \n86: **Landing Page Patterns:**\n87: - Prominent search bar with city/address input\n88: - \"Popular Searches\" links to major cities\n89: - Featured neighborhoods/properties\n90: - Rental tools: Rent calculator, moving center, neighborhood guides\n91: - \"Find Apartments by State\" directory grid\n92: \n93: **Search/Listing Page Patterns:**\n94: - Filter-heavy sidebar: Price, Beds, Baths, Property Type, Amenities (checkboxes), Pet Policy, Transit Score, Rating\n95: - Sort options: Best Match, Price (Low to High), Price (High to Low), Most Recent\n96: - Property cards: Photo, price, address, bed/bath, sqft, \"Available Now\" badge, rating stars\n97: - Map/list toggle view\n98: - \"Save\" button per card\n99: \n100: **Detail Page Patterns:**\n101: - Large photo gallery with thumbnail strip\n102: - Floor plan section (image uploads)\n103: - Amenities grid with checkmarks\n104: - Map with nearby points of interest (transit, restaurants, schools)\n105: - Contact sidebar: Phone, Email, Schedule Tour, Apply Online\n106: - Price history and availability timeline\n107: \n108: **Admin/Manager Dashboard (Apartments.com Manager):**\n109: - Property portfolio overview\n110: - Listing performance stats (views, leads, inquiries)\n111: - Lead/inquiry inbox with statuses (New, Contacted, Tour Scheduled)\n112: - Property listing editor (photos, description, pricing, availability)\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ### Competitor 3: Redfin Rentals (redfin.com/rentals)\n117: \n118: **Type:** Full real estate platform (sales + rentals), Redfin-owned\n119: **USP:** Operated by brokerage; unified renter/buyer/seller dashboard; \"Renter Dashboard\" for saved searches and application tracking\n120: \n121: **Live analysis (2026-05-19):**\n122: \n123: **Universal Gateway Approach:**\n124: - Redfin homepage serves Buy, Rent, Sell, Mortgage, and Agent discovery under one roof\n125: - Primary nav: Buy, Rent, Sell, Mortgage, Real Estate Agents — each with dropdown submenus\n126: - Hero section: \"Redfin Early Access. Find it first.\" with tabbed CTAs (Buy, Mortgage, Sell, Rent)\n127: - Each CTA tab has its own visual, copy, and link\n128: \n129: **Rental-specific Navigation & Pages:**\n130: - Dedicated Rent top-nav dropdown with: Renter dashboard, Rental market tracker, \"How much rent can I afford?\", \"Should I rent or buy?\", Renter guide, \"List my home for rent\", \"Rental Tools dashboard\", \"US rental market trends\"\n131: - User dropdown (signed-in): Feed, Favorites & comments, Saved searches, My homes, Renter dashboard, My Redfin agent, Appointments, Open house schedule\n132: \n133: **Landing Page Sections (redfin.com):**\n134: 1. **Hero + Tabs** — \"Redfin Early Access. Find it first.\" with 4 action cards (Buy, Mortgage, Sell, Rent). Each has icon image + headline + description + CTA button.\n135: 2. **App Download** — Phone mockup + QR code + \"Get the Redfin app\" with brief copy\n136: 3. **Talk to a Redfin Agent** — \"Where are you searching for homes?\" input + assurance (\"no pressure or obligation\")\n137: 4. **Latest Homes Grid** — City name grid cards: \"Browse the newest homes from around the country\" with ~20 city links\n138: 5. **City/State Browse Links** — Alphabetical city links + state links for SEO and discovery\n139: 6. **Footer** — 4-column structure: Join us (Agent, Referrals, Careers), Find homes faster (app badges), About us (Why Redfin, Community, Inclusion, Culture, Blog), Find us (Contact, Help), Subsidiaries (Rent., ApartmentGuide), Affiliated Business (Rocket Close, Rocket Mortgage)\n140: \n141: **Key Insights:**\n142: - Renter Dashboard is a first-class navigation item (not buried)\n143: - Financial tools are deeply integrated (rent affordability calculator, rent vs. buy calculator)\n144: - Strong cross-promotion with Redfin agent network and mortgage services\n145: - Desktop-first with prominent app download CTAs\n146: \n147: **Design Lessons for NestFind:**\n148: - Consider rent affordability calculator as a differentiator\n149: - Make \"Favorites\" a top-level nav item from the start\n150: - Rental-specific content (market trends, renter guides) drives SEO and engagement\n151: \n152: ---\n153: \n154: ### Competitor 5: Airbnb (airbnb.com)\n155: \n156: **Type:** Short-term rental marketplace\n157: **USP:** Best-in-class UX, immersive design, host/guest marketplace\n158: \n159: **Landing Page Patterns:**\n160: - Category bar (horizontal scroll chips): Rooms, Mansions, Amazing pools, Cabins, etc.\n161: - Card grid with large photos, location name, distance, dates, price per night\n162: - Each card: Carousel of photos, heart (wishlist) button, location, host type, rating, price\n163: - Search: \"Where\", \"Check in / Check out\" (date picker), \"Who\" (guests selector)\n164: - \"Inspiration for your next trip\" sections (themed, curated)\n165: \n166: **Detail Page Patterns:**\n167: - Full-width immersive photo gallery with \"Show all photos\" button\n168: - Title, rating, location, host info in header\n169: - Sectioned below: Description, What this place offers (amenities with icons), Where you'll sleep (bedroom breakdown), Map, Host info, Things to know (house rules)\n170: - Right sidebar: Price, date picker, guest selector, \"Reserve\" CTA, total calculation\n171: - Wishlist/save functionality (heart icon)\n172: \n173: **Key Design Lessons:**\n174: - Immersive, photo-first design\n175: - Card carousels on search results pages\n176: - Sectioned, scannable detail pages\n177: - Sticky booking/reserve sidebar (or bottom bar on mobile)\n178: - Trust-building elements: host profiles, reviews, verified badges\n179: \n180: ---\n181: \n182: ### Competitor 4: Rent.com (rent.com)\n183: \n184: **Type:** Rental-only marketplace (Redfin subsidiary since 2012)\n185: **USP:** Focused exclusively on rentals (no sales), strong brand recognition as \"Rent.\"\n186: \n187: **Live analysis (2026-05-19):**\n188: \n189: **Landing Page Structure:**\n190: 1. **Top Nav** — Logo, Saved (0 badge), List a Property, Business Solutions, Moving Center, Log In, Sign Up\n191: 2. **Hero** — \"Find your perfect place.\" + large search input + trending properties card grid\n192: 3. **\"Properties for you\"** — Grid of trending/featured property cards with: property image (3:2 ratio), price, name/address, bed/bath summary, badges (\"$55 Price Drop\", \"1 Month Free!\", \"Popular\")\n193: 4. **\"Renter tips and insights\"** — Blog card grid with 3 articles: \"11 Steps to Follow When Renting an Apartment\", \"Rent Calculator: How Much Should You Spend on Rent?\", \"The Best US Cities for Hybrid Work\"\n194: 5. **\"Popular Searches\"** — Structured browse directory organized as: Rentals Near Me, Apartments For Rent By City (~50 cities), Houses For Rent By City (~80 cities), Rentals By State (all 50)\n195: 6. **\"The fastest way to rent a home is with the app\"** — Strong mobile app promotion with app store badges, QR code, \"Scan to get the app\"\n196: 7. **Footer** — 4-column: Our Company (Redfin.com, Blog, Research, Legal), Popular Searches (8 categories), Let Us Help (App, Avoid Scams, List Property, Business Solutions, Rent Estimator, Accessibility), App badges\n197: \n198: **Property Card Pattern (Rent.com):**\n199: - Image: ~400x270px, 3:2 ratio\n200: - Badges on image: \"$55 Price Drop\" (green), \"1 Month Free!\" (blue), \"Popular\" (orange)\n201: - Below image: Price (large, bold), Property name, Address (street + city/state/ZIP), Bed/Bath (e.g., \"1–2 Beds • 1–2 Baths\")\n202: - No heart/favorite icon visible on cards (favoriting may require signed-in state)\n203: \n204: **Key Insight:** Rent.com uses badges aggressively on property cards to highlight deals and urgency — Price Drop, Month Free, and Popular badges create FOMO and scanability.\n205: \n206: **Design Lessons for NestFind:**\n207: - Property card badges (Price Reduced, New Listing, Popular) increase engagement\n208: - Blog/resource section establishes authority and improves SEO\n209: - Browse-by-directory structure (city/state hierarchy) is critical for SEO traffic\n210: \n211: ---\n212: \n213: ### Competitor 6: Rentable (rentable.co)\n214: \n215: **Type:** Rental marketplace with verified listings focus\n216: **USP:** Human-verified listings, budget calculator, mobile-first\n217: \n218: **Landing Page Patterns:**\n219: - Hero: \"Every Apartment Near You, In One Place\" + city search input\n220: - Listing count prominently displayed: \"Browse 10,377,478 apartments\"\n221: - Grid of popular cities with images\n222: - Grid of \"Apartments for Rent Near College Campuses\"\n223: - Testimonials and press mentions (Curbed, NBC Today)\n224: - Mobile app promotion with ratings (4.7 Apple, 3.6 Google Play)\n225: - Rent affordability calculator CTA\n226: - \"Real Apartments, Verified by Real People\" trust section\n227: - \"What is Rentable?\" about section\n228: - \"Advertising a Property?\" partner CTA\n229: - Trusted by: Forbes, MarketWatch, CNBC, Realtor.com, Washington Post logos\n230: \n231: **Key Design Lessons:**\n232: - Social proof sections (press mentions, trust logos, ratings)\n233: - City/campus browse grids for SEO and discovery\n234: - Clear value proposition: \"Every Apartment Near You, In One Place\"\n235: - Strong mobile-first design\n236: \n237: ---\n238: \n239: ### Competitor 7: HotPads (hotpads.com)\n240: \n241: **Type:** Map-centric rental search (owned by Zillow Group)\n242: **USP:** Map-first browsing experience with polygon search\n243: \n244: **Landing Page Patterns:**\n245: - Minimal: search + city links\n246: - No landing \"page\" — immediately drops users into map search\n247: \n248: **Search/Listing Page Patterns:**\n249: - Full-screen map as primary interface\n250: - Listing cards overlay on top of map\n251: - Polygon search (draw area on map)\n252: - Filter bar: Price, Beds, Property Type, More\n253: - Color-coded map pins by price tier\n254: - \"My HotPads\" section: Saved searches, saved listings\n255: \n256: **Key Design Lessons:**\n257: - Map as the primary interface (alternative to card-first approach)\n258: - Minimal design with high information density on map\n259: \n260: ---\n261: \n262: ## Competitive Positioning Summary\n263: \n264: | Dimension | Zillow | Apartments.com | Redfin | Rent.com | NestFind Opportunity |\n265: |-----------|--------|---------------|--------|----------|----------------------|\n266: | Primary focus | Sales + Rentals | Rentals | Sales + Rentals | Rentals only | **Rentals only** |\n267: | Search UX | Map+List split | Filter-heavy sidebar | Tabbed gateway | Trending cards | **Clean, ad-free browsing** |\n268: | Mobile experience | App-centric | Web-responsive | App-centric | App-centric | **Responsive-first web** |\n269: | Renter dashboard | Full hub (apps, payments) | Basic save | Full dashboard | Save/search | **Simple favorites + inquiries** |\n270: | Inquiry/Contact | Apply now + Tour request | Contact sidebar | Agent-mediated | Contact/apply | **Direct inquiry form** |\n271: | Admin dashboard | Property Manager tool | Apartments.com Manager | Rental Tools dashboard | List a Property | **Clean admin panel (MVP)** |\n272: | Ad load | Moderate | High | Low | Moderate | **Zero ads (key differentiator)** |\n273: | Trust signals | Reviews, Zestimate | Ratings | Agent reviews | Deals, badges | **Verified listings + clean UI** |\n274: | Listing quality | Aggregated | Aggregated | MLS+Aggregated | Aggregated | **Curated/admin-managed** |\n275: \n276: ---\n277: \n278: ## Reference UI Patterns\n279: \n280: ### Pattern 1: Property Search Card\n281: \n282: **Present in 100% of competitors.** The standard rental property card contains:\n283: \n284: | Element | Typical Size/Position | Prevalence |\n285: |---------|----------------------|------------|\n286: | Primary photo (thumbnail) | Top, ~280-340px width, 16:9 or 4:3 ratio | 100% |\n287: | Price | Large, bold, top-right or bottom-left of photo | 100% |\n288: | Address/Location | Below photo, primary text | 100% |\n289: | Bed/Bath Count | Below photo, secondary text (e.g., \"2 bd | 1 ba\") | 100% |\n290: | Square Footage | Below photo, secondary text | 80% |\n291: | Property Type Badge | On photo overlay (e.g., \"Apartment\", \"Condo\") | 60% |\n292: | Favorite/Heart Toggle | Top-right corner of card or photo | 80% |\n293: | Deal/Status Badge | On photo overlay (e.g., \"Price Drop\", \"1 Month Free\", \"Popular\", \"New\") | 60% |\n294: | \"New\" or \"Available Now\" Badge | On photo overlay | 50% |\n295: | Rating Stars | Below photo (if reviews available) | 30% |\n296: | Photo Count | On photo (e.g., \"1/12\" or \"📷 12\") | 70% |\n297: | \"Contact\" / \"Apply\" CTA | Bottom of card or hover overlay | 60% |\n298: \n299: ### Pattern 2: Search Filter Panel\n300: \n301: **Present in 100% of competitors.** Standard filter hierarchy:\n302: \n303: 1. **Location** (text input, autocomplete) — always first\n304: 2. **Price Range** (min-max sliders or inputs) — always present\n305: 3. **Bedrooms** (dropdown: Studio, 1+, 2+, 3+, 4+) — always present\n306: 4. **Property Type** (checkboxes: Apartment, House, Condo, Townhouse, Studio) — always present\n307: 5. **Bathrooms** (dropdown: 1+, 1.5+, 2+, 3+) — present in ~80%\n308: 6. **Amenities** (checkboxes: In-unit laundry, Parking, Pet-friendly, AC, Gym, Pool, etc.) — present in ~90%\n309: 7. **Square Footage** (range) — present in ~50%\n310: 8. **Move-in Date** (date picker) — present in ~30%\n311: 9. **Sort** (Best Match, Price Low/High, Newest, Rating) — always present\n312: 10. **\"Save Search\"** button — present in ~70%\n313: \n314: ### Pattern 3: Photo Gallery (Detail Page)\n315: \n316: **Present in 100% of competitors.** Standard patterns:\n317: \n318: - **Hero Gallery:** Large featured image with left/right arrows for navigation\n319: - **Thumbnail Strip:** Row of smaller thumbnails below hero for quick selection\n320: - **\"View All Photos\" Button:** Opens full-screen lightbox gallery\n321: - **Photo Count Badge:** e.g., \"1/12\" or \"Show all 12 photos\"\n322: - **Floor Plan Section:** Separate from photo gallery, often with interactive zoom\n323: - **Virtual Tour / 3D Tour Link:** Increasingly common (Apartments.com, Zillow)\n324: \n325: ### Pattern 4: Map Integration\n326: \n327: **Present in 95% of competitors.**\n328: \n329: - **Embedded Map (Detail Page):** Google Maps iframe with property pin marker; often shows nearby points of interest (transit, schools, restaurants)\n330: - **Map/Split View (Search Page):** Left panel = card list, right panel = full map; pins update as map pans; drawn area search\n331: - **Map Pin Design:** Custom marker with price overlay (Zillow), color-coded by price tier (HotPads)\n332: \n333: ### Pattern 5: Favorites / Saved Properties\n334: \n335: **Present in 90% of competitors.**\n336: \n337: - Heart icon toggle on property cards and detail page header\n338: - \"Saved\" or \"Favorites\" page: grid/list of favorited properties\n339: - Requires authentication (guest users prompted to sign in)\n340: - Often named \"Saved Homes,\" \"Favorites,\" or \"Saved Properties\"\n341: - May show count badge in navigation (Zillow: \"Favorites (3)\")\n342: \n343: ### Pattern 6: Inquiry / Contact Form\n344: \n345: **Present in 100% of competitors.** Standard fields: Name, Email, Phone (optional), Message. Submitted to property manager. Typically a modal or sidebar form.\n346: \n347: ### Pattern 7: Admin Dashboard (Property Management)\n348: \n349: **Based on Behance/Dribbble research of property management dashboard designs (~20 analyzed projects):**\n350: \n351: Standard dashboard elements:\n352: - **Sidebar Navigation:** Dashboard, Properties, Inquiries/Messages, Users, Settings, Reports\n353: - **Top Bar:** Search, Notifications bell, User avatar + dropdown\n354: - **Overview Stats Cards:** Total Properties, Active Listings, Total Inquiries, Pending Responses, Total Users — displayed as 4-6 metric cards with icon, value, label, trend indicator\n355: - **Recent Activity Feed:** Timeline of recent inquiries, new user registrations, listing changes\n356: - **Properties Table:** Columns: Photo (40px thumb), Title, Type, Price, Status (Active/Archived/Draft), Bed/Bath, Date Added, Actions (Edit, Delete, View). With search, filter, sort, pagination.\n357: - **Inquiry Table:** Columns: Name, Email, Property, Date, Status (New/Read/Responded), Actions (View, Reply, Mark Read)\n358: - **Users Table:** Renter list with Name, Email, Join Date, Status (Active/Suspended), Actions\n359: - **Property Editor:** Form with sections: Basic Info, Location/Address, Pricing, Details (beds, baths, sqft, type), Amenities (checkboxes grouped by category), Photos (multi-upload with drag-drop, reorder, preview), Floor Plan upload. Submit/Cancel buttons.\n360: - **Inquiry Detail/Response View:** Original inquiry message + reply textarea + Mark as Read/Responded status change + Send Reply button\n361: \n362: ---\n363: \n364: ## Page-type Conventions\n365: \n366: ### Landing Page\n367: \n368: **Standard Sections (present in 80%+ of competitors):**\n369: \n370: | # | Section | Purpose | Prevalence | NestFind Applicability |\n371: |---|---------|---------|------------|------------------------|\n372: | 1 | **Navigation Bar** | Logo, nav links, Sign In / Join CTAs | 100% | Required |\n373: | 2 | **Hero + Search** | Primary search input (city/address) + value prop tagline + CTA | 100% | Required — NestFind's primary entry point |\n374: | 3 | **Popular Cities / Quick Links** | Grid of city images linking to pre-filtered searches | 80% | Recommended for SEO and discovery |\n375: | 4 | **How It Works** | 3-step diagram explaining search → find → apply | 70% | Recommended for first-time users |\n376: | 5 | **Featured Properties** | Carousel or grid of curated listings | 60% | Optional — depends on having listings to feature |\n377: | 6 | **Value Props / Features** | Icon + text cards explaining platform benefits | 90% | Required |\n378: | 7 | **Trust / Social Proof** | Testimonials, press logos, review ratings, user counts | 80% | Recommended for credibility |\n379: | 8 | **Budget Calculator CTA** | \"How much rent can I afford?\" tool link | 40% | Differentiator opportunity |\n380: | 9 | **Mobile App Promotion** | App store badges, phone mockup, QR code | 50% | Optional (web-first) |\n381: | 10 | **For Property Managers** | CTA to list properties or advertise | 60% | Important if NestFind has property manager acquisition |\n382: | 11 | **Footer** | About, Contact, Terms, Privacy, Social links | 100% | Required |\n383: \n384: **Key Takeaway:** The hero + search bar is the single most important element. Every rental platform's landing page centers around the search input. Secondary sections build trust and explain value.\n385: \n386: ### Dashboard (Renter Hub)\n387: \n388: **Standard Elements (based on Zillow Renter Hub + design patterns):**\n389: \n390: | # | Element | Purpose | Prevalence |\n391: |---|---------|---------|------------|\n392: | 1 | **Saved Searches** | Quick access to active searches with new listing counts | 80% |\n393: | 2 | **Favorites Grid** | Preview of saved properties with quick remove | 70% |\n394: | 3 | **Messages/Inquiries Inbox** | List of sent inquiries with response statuses | 60% |\n395: | 4 | **Application Status** | Track submitted applications | 50% |\n396: | 5 | **Recommended Properties** | Algorithmic suggestions based on saved searches | 50% |\n397: \n398: **NestFind Renter Dashboard should include:** Saved Properties (favorites), Active Inquiries (sent messages), Saved Searches (optional), Account Settings link.\n399: \n400: ### Dashboard (Admin)\n401: \n402: **Standard Elements (based on Behance/Dribbble analysis):**\n403: \n404: | # | Element | Purpose | Prevalence |\n405: |---|---------|---------|------------|\n406: | 1 | **Stats Overview Cards** | Total Properties, Active/Archived, Total Inquiries, Total Users | 100% |\n407: | 2 | **Recent Inquiries** | Latest 5-10 inquiries with status badges and quick-view | 90% |\n408: | 3 | **Quick Actions** | \"Add Property\" button, \"View All Inquiries\" link | 80% |\n409: | 4 | **Properties Table** | Full CRUD list with search, filter, pagination | 100% |\n410: | 5 | **Property Create/Edit Form** | Multi-section form (photos, details, amenities, location) | 100% |\n411: | 6 | **Inquiries Table** | List with status filters (New, Read, Responded) | 100% |\n412: | 7 | **Inquiry Response View** | Message thread + reply form + status change | 80% |\n413: | 8 | **Users Table** | Renter list with status, activity, suspension toggle | 90% |\n414: | 9 | **Sidebar Navigation** | Collapsible sidebar with icons + labels | 100% |\n415: | 10 | **Top Bar** | Search, notifications, admin avatar dropdown | 90% |\n416: \n417: **Admin Dashboard Layout Convention:** Sidebar (200-250px) + Main Content Area. Stats cards in a horizontal row at top. Table or list below. \"Add New\" FAB or top-right button.\n418: \n419: ### Property Detail Page\n420: \n421: **Standard Sections (present in 90%+ of competitors):**\n422: \n423: | # | Section | Content | Prevalence |\n424: |---|---------|---------|------------|\n425: | 1 | **Photo Gallery** | Hero image + thumbnail strip + \"View all photos\" link | 100% |\n426: | 2 | **Header** | Title, address, price, bed/bath/sqft summary | 100% |\n427: | 3 | **Description** | Free-text property description paragraph(s) | 100% |\n428: | 4 | **Amenities Grid** | Icon + label grid (2-4 columns) | 95% |\n429: | 5 | **Floor Plan** | Floor plan image with zoom capability | 60% |\n430: | 6 | **Property Details/Specs** | Table: Type, Year Built, Deposit, Lease Terms, Pets, Parking | 80% |\n431: | 7 | **Location Map** | Embedded Google Map with pin | 95% |\n432: | 8 | **Inquiry/Contact** | Form (name, email, phone, message) + \"Send\" CTA | 100% |\n433: | 9 | **Favorite Toggle** | Heart icon for saving/unsaving | 90% |\n434: | 10 | **Similar/Related Properties** | Card row of suggested properties nearby | 50% |\n435: \n436: **Layout Convention:** Two-column layout — Main content (70%) left, Sidebar (30%) right. Sidebar is typically sticky and contains the inquiry form or contact CTA. On mobile, stacks to single column; inquiry CTA becomes a sticky bottom bar. Photo gallery always at top, full-width.\n437: \n438: ### Auth Pages (Login / Register)\n439: \n440: **Standard Patterns:**\n441: \n442: | # | Pattern | Details | Prevalence |\n443: |---|---------|---------|------------|\n444: | 1 | **Split-screen layout** | Left: brand/gradient, Right: form | 60% |\n445: | 2 | **Centered card layout** | Form in white card centered on colored background | 40% |\n446: | 3 | **Email + Password fields** | Full-width inputs, 48px height | 100% |\n447: | 4 | **Social login buttons** | Google, Apple, Facebook | 70% |\n448: | 5 | **\"Forgot Password\" link** | Below password field | 100% |\n449: | 6 | **\"Don't have an account? Sign up\"** | Below form | 100% |\n450: | 7 | **Password show/hide toggle** | Eye icon in password field right side | 70% |\n451: \n452: ---\n453: \n454: ## PRD Reference Analysis\n455: \n456: | PRD Feature | Reference Source | Dominant UI Pattern | NestFind Implication |\n457: |-------------|-----------------|---------------------|---------------------|\n458: | Property search with filters | Zillow, Apartments.com | Map+list split, filter panel, property cards | Implement card+filter pattern; map is nice-to-have for v1 |\n459: | Property detail with photo gallery | Zillow, Airbnb | Full-width hero image, thumbnail strip, sectioned content below | Photo-first design; gallery with thumbnails |\n460: | Google Maps integration | Zillow, Apartments.com | Embedded map section with pin on detail page; optionally on search | Detail page map is mandatory |\n461: | Favorites / Save properties | Zillow, Airbnb | Heart icon toggle; dedicated Saved/Favorites page | Heart toggle on cards + detail page; Favorites page |\n462: | Inquiry / Contact form | Zillow, Apartments.com | Sidebar form or modal; name, email, phone, message + Send CTA | Sidebar on detail page; confirmation toast |\n463: | Admin property management | Dashboard patterns on Behance/Dribbble | Sidebar + table + multi-section form; stats cards | Follow standard admin dashboard layout |\n464: | Admin inquiry management | Apartments.com Manager, Behance | Table with status badges (New/Read/Responded), inline reply | Table with status filters, reply view |\n465: | Admin user management | Dashboard patterns | Table with status (Active/Suspended) + action buttons | Model after Stripe-style user tables |\n466: | Renter registration | Zillow, Airbnb | \"Join\" / \"Sign Up\" — email, name, password, optional phone | Simple form; social login optional for v1 |\n467: \n468: ---\n469: \n470: ## Design Gap Analysis\n471: \n472: **What competitors do well:**\n473: - Photo-first, immersive browsing experience\n474: - Map integration as core discovery mechanism\n475: - Robust, responsive filter panels\n476: - Trust-building elements (verified listings, reviews, badges)\n477: \n478: **What competitors do poorly (opportunity for NestFind):**\n479: - Ad-heavy interfaces that clutter the browsing experience\n480: - Overly complex filter panels that overwhelm casual renters\n481: - Slow page loads due to heavy tracking scripts\n482: - Poor mobile inquiry/applications flow\n483: \n484: **NestFind differentiators to emphasize in design:**\n485: 1. **Clean, ad-free browsing** — minimal, focused UI\n486: 2. **Streamlined inquiry flow** — simple contact form, no multi-step applications\n487: 3. **Quick favorites** — fast toggle without friction\n488: 4. **Simple admin dashboard** — focused on essential management tasks, not bloated with upsells\n489: 5. **Mobile-responsive as first principle** — not an afterthought\n490: \n491: ---\n492: \n493: *End of Domain Research. Proceed to Phase 3: Design Guide generation.*\n\n(End of file - total 493 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Domain Research — NestFind\n\n**Generated:** 2026-05-19\n**Updated:** 2026-05-19 (live competitor site analysis)\n**Source:** Phase 2.5 — Domain & Reference Research\n**Purpose:** Identify standard UI patterns and essential sections from top rental property listing platforms before Design Guide generation.\n**Competitors analyzed live:** Zillow (zillow.com), Redfin (redfin.com), Rent.com (rent.com)\n\n---\n\n## Industry\n\n**Domain:** Real Estate / Rental Property Listings\n\nNestFind operates in the digital rental marketplace vertical — a subset of PropTech (Property Technology) focused exclusively on long-term residential rentals (as opposed to short-term/vacation rentals or property sales). The platform connects renters with available properties through search, discovery, detail views, favorites, and inquiry submission.\n\n**Market Context:**\n- The US online rental market is dominated by Zillow Rentals, Apartments.com, and Realtor.com Rentals\n- Mobile-first search behavior is standard — renters browse on mobile, apply on desktop\n- Key differentiator for newer entrants: streamlined UX, fewer ads, verified listings, built-in application/inquiry flows","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md","time":{"start":1779182192164,"end":1779182192451}},"id":"prt_e3f85c0600012Czh8E1VejW2bp","sessionID":"ses_1c07a6546ffe7dcCAj21iQXRj5","messageID":"msg_e3f859ee90010HYUJhmLTYQAau"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779182194295,"sessionID":"ses_1c07a6546ffe7dcCAj21iQXRj5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_9Cy4jIoolQxtwlJ4OeLl3894","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: ### Application Purpose\n6: \n7: NestFind is a streamlined rental property listing platform that connects renters with available properties. The platform focuses exclusively on rentals, providing a clean and efficient browsing experience where renters can search, filter, view details, save favorites, and submit inquiries to property managers. An accompanying admin dashboard enables administrators to manage property listings, respond to inquiries, and oversee user accounts.\n8: \n9: The platform targets two primary user groups: Renters who browse and discover rental properties, and Administrators who manage the listings and respond to renter inquiries. NestFind integrates with Google Maps for property location display.\n10: \n11: ### Technology Stack\n12: \n13: | Layer | Technology |\n14: |-------|------------|\n15: | Backend | NestJS 11, TypeScript 5.7+ |\n16: | Frontend | React 19 with React Router 7 (framework mode) |\n17: | Database | PostgreSQL 16 |\n18: | ORM | TypeORM 0.3.x |\n19: | Authentication | JWT via httpOnly cookies (Access: 1h, Refresh: 7d) |\n20: | API Documentation | Swagger/OpenAPI |\n21: | Validation | class-validator (backend), Zod (frontend) |\n22: | Frontend State | Redux Toolkit with createAsyncThunk |\n23: | Styling | Tailwind CSS 4, Shadcn/UI |\n24: | Maps | Google Maps API |\n25: | Deployment | Docker |\n26: \n27: ### Domain\n28: \n29: `nestfind.com` — web application\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## User Roles\n34: \n35: | Role | Description | Permissions |\n36: |------|-------------|-------------|\n37: | **Renter** | Browses rental property listings, views detailed property information, saves properties to favorites, and submits inquiries to property managers. | `browse_properties`, `view_property_details`, `save_favorites`, `submit_inquiries` |\n38: | **Admin** | Has full system access to manage property listings (CRUD), manage user accounts, view and respond to inquiries from renters. | `manage_properties`, `manage_users`, `view_inquiries`, `respond_to_inquiries` |\n39: | **Guest** | Unauthenticated visitor who can browse public property listings and view property details. Must register/login to save favorites or submit inquiries. | `browse_properties`, `view_property_details` |\n40: \n41: ### Authentication & Authorization\n42: \n43: - **JWT via httpOnly cookies**: Access token (1 hour) + Refresh token (7 days). Cookies configured with `httpOnly: true, secure: true, sameSite: 'strict'`. Tokens are never stored in localStorage.\n44: - **Role-based access control (RBAC)**: Guards at the route/endpoint level enforce role-specific permissions via `JwtAuthGuard` + `RolesGuard`.\n45: - **Guest access**: Public endpoints for browsing and viewing properties are marked with `@Public()` decorator; all other endpoints require authentication.\n46: - **Admin assignment**: Admin accounts are created by existing admins or via database seeding. Self-registration defaults to Renter role.\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## Core Features\n51: \n52: ### Common (All Users)\n53: \n54: - **Authentication**\n55:   - User login with email + password\n56:   - JWT access token (1h) and refresh token (7d) via httpOnly cookies\n57:   - Token refresh mechanism with rotation\n58:   - Logout clears cookies\n59: \n60: - **Registration**\n61:   - Self-service sign-up with name, email, password, phone (optional)\n62:   - Default role assignment: Renter\n63:   - Email verification (optional, configurable)\n64: \n65: - **Password Reset**\n66:   - Forgot password flow via email\n67:   - Secure reset token with expiration\n68: \n69: ### Renter Features\n70: \n71: 1. **Property Search**\n72:    - Search by location (text input or current geolocation)\n73:    - Real-time filtering by price range, number of bedrooms, property type\n74:    - Results displayed as property cards with thumbnail, price, and key details\n75:    - Pagination or infinite scroll for large result sets\n76: \n77: 2. **Property Detail View**\n78:    - Full property page with photo gallery, amenities list, description, and floor plan\n79:    - Embedded Google Map showing property location\n80:    - Save to favorites (toggle)\n81:    - Contact / Submit Inquiry button\n82: \n83: 3. **Favorites Management**\n84:    - View all saved/favorited properties\n85:    - Remove properties from favorites\n86:    - Quick access from navigation\n87: \n88: 4. **Submit Inquiry**\n89:    - Contact form on property detail page (name, email, phone, message)\n90:    - Form validation before submission\n91:    - Confirmation message shown to renter\n92:    - Admin notified of new inquiry\n93: \n94: ### Admin Features\n95: \n96: 1. **Admin Dashboard**\n97:    - Overview statistics: total properties, total inquiries, recent activity\n98:    - Quick links to property management and inquiry management\n99: \n100: 2. **Property Management (CRUD)**\n101:    - List all properties with search, filter, and pagination\n102:    - Add new property with details: title, description, price, bedrooms, bathrooms, property type, address, amenities, photos (multi-upload)\n103:    - Edit existing property information\n104:    - Delete or archive property listings (soft delete)\n105: \n106: 3. **Inquiry Management**\n107:    - View all inquiries with status (new, read, responded)\n108:    - Mark inquiries as read\n109:    - Respond to inquiries directly from the dashboard\n110:    - Filter by property or renter\n111: \n112: 4. **User Management**\n113:    - View list of registered renters\n114:    - View renter details and activity history\n115:    - Suspend or reactivate user accounts\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ## Functional Requirements\n120: \n121: ### Authentication\n122: \n123: - **FR-AUTH-001**: Users must authenticate with email and password to access protected features.\n124: - **FR-AUTH-002**: JWT access tokens expire after 1 hour; refresh tokens expire after 7 days.\n125: - **FR-AUTH-003**: Refresh tokens are rotated on each use (old token invalidated).\n126: - **FR-AUTH-004**: All authentication tokens are stored in httpOnly, secure, sameSite-strict cookies.\n127: - **FR-AUTH-005**: Guest users can browse properties without authentication.\n128: \n129: ### Property Search\n130: \n131: - **FR-SEARCH-001**: Renters can search properties by location text (city, neighborhood, zip code).\n132: - **FR-SEARCH-002**: Renters can use browser geolocation to find properties near their current location.\n133: - **FR-SEARCH-003**: Results support filtering by price range (min/max), number of bedrooms, and property type.\n134: - **FR-SEARCH-004**: Filters update results in real-time without full page reload.\n135: - **FR-SEARCH-005**: Each result card displays thumbnail image, price, address, bedrooms, and bathrooms.\n136: \n137: ### Property Details\n138: \n139: - **FR-DETAIL-001**: Property detail page displays full photo gallery with navigation.\n140: - **FR-DETAIL-002**: Property page includes description, amenities list, pricing, and property specifications.\n141: - **FR-DETAIL-003**: An embedded Google Map shows the property location with a pin marker.\n142: - **FR-DETAIL-004**: Authenticated renters can toggle the property as a favorite.\n143: - **FR-DETAIL-005**: A Contact/Inquiry button is prominently displayed.\n144: \n145: ### Inquiries\n146: \n147: - **FR-INQ-001**: Inquiry form collects name, email, phone (optional), and message.\n148: - **FR-INQ-002**: Form fields are validated client-side (Zod) and server-side (class-validator).\n149: - **FR-INQ-003**: On successful submission, renter sees a confirmation message.\n150: - **FR-INQ-004**: System notifies admin of new inquiries (in-dashboard notification).\n151: \n152: ### Admin: Property Management\n153: \n154: - **FR-ADM-PROP-001**: Admin can create new property listings with all required fields.\n155: - **FR-ADM-PROP-002**: Admin can upload multiple photos per property.\n156: - **FR-ADM-PROP-003**: Admin can edit all fields of an existing property.\n157: - **FR-ADM-PROP-004**: Admin can soft-delete (archive) a property listing.\n158: - **FR-ADM-PROP-005**: Property list supports search, sort, and pagination.\n159: \n160: ### Admin: Inquiry Management\n161: \n162: - **FR-ADM-INQ-001**: Admin can view all inquiries with status indicators.\n163: - **FR-ADM-INQ-002**: Admin can filter inquiries by property or renter.\n164: - **FR-ADM-INQ-003**: Admin can mark inquiries as read and respond to them.\n165: \n166: ### Admin: User Management\n167: \n168: - **FR-ADM-USER-001**: Admin can view a list of all registered renters.\n169: - **FR-ADM-USER-002**: Admin can view individual renter details and activity.\n170: - **FR-ADM-USER-003**: Admin can suspend or reactivate user accounts.\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ## Non-Functional Requirements\n175: \n176: ### Performance\n177: \n178: - **NFR-PERF-001**: Property search results must return within 500ms for typical query loads.\n179: - **NFR-PERF-002**: Image assets should be served with lazy loading and optimized formats (WebP).\n180: - **NFR-PERF-003**: API responses must use pagination for list endpoints (default: 20 items/page).\n181: \n182: ### Security\n183: \n184: - **NFR-SEC-001**: All authenticated endpoints enforce JWT validation via guards.\n185: - **NFR-SEC-002**: Passwords are hashed using bcrypt with appropriate salt rounds.\n186: - **NFR-SEC-003**: Input validation is enforced at the API boundary using class-validator/Zod.\n187: - **NFR-SEC-004**: CORS is configured to allow only the frontend origin.\n188: - **NFR-SEC-005**: Rate limiting is applied to authentication endpoints (login, register, password reset).\n189: \n190: ### Reliability\n191: \n192: - **NFR-REL-001**: Database operations use transactions for multi-step mutations.\n193: - **NFR-REL-002**: Soft delete (`deleted_at`) is used for properties and user accounts (no destructive deletes).\n194: - **NFR-REL-003**: API errors return consistent response format with appropriate HTTP status codes.\n195: \n196: ### Maintainability\n197: \n198: - **NFR-MAIN-001**: Backend follows the 4-layer architecture pattern: Controller → Service → Repository → Entity.\n199: - **NFR-MAIN-002**: All backend layers extend base classes (`BaseController`, `BaseService`, `BaseRepository`, `BaseEntity`).\n200: - **NFR-MAIN-003**: Frontend follows file organization patterns defined in `.claude/react/docs/file-organization.md`.\n201: - **NFR-MAIN-004**: All API endpoints are documented with Swagger/OpenAPI annotations.\n202: \n203: ### Compatibility\n204: \n205: - **NFR-COMP-001**: Frontend supports latest 2 versions of Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge.\n206: - **NFR-COMP-002**: Application is responsive and functional on mobile, tablet, and desktop viewports.\n207: \n208: ---\n209: \n210: ## Ontology / Glossary\n211: \n212: | Term | Definition |\n213: |------|------------|\n214: | **Property** | A rental property listing with details such as title, description, price, address, bedrooms, bathrooms, property type, amenities, and photos. |\n215: | **Property Type** | The category of rental property (e.g., apartment, house, condo, townhouse, studio). |\n216: | **Listing** | A published property that is visible to renters in search results. |\n217: | **Renter** | A registered user who browses, searches, and saves properties, and submits inquiries. |\n218: | **Admin** | A system administrator with full access to manage properties, users, and inquiries. |\n219: | **Guest** | An unauthenticated visitor who can browse and view property details. |\n220: | **Inquiry** | A contact form submission from a renter about a specific property, containing name, email, phone (optional), and message. |\n221: | **Favorites** | A saved collection of properties that a renter has bookmarked for later reference. |\n222: | **Amenity** | A feature or facility available at a property (e.g., parking, laundry, gym, pool, air conditioning). |\n223: | **Soft Delete** | A record is marked as deleted (`deleted_at` timestamp) but remains in the database, allowing recovery and audit trails. |\n224: | **Archive** | A property listing that has been soft-deleted by an admin, removing it from public search results. |\n225: | **httpOnly Cookie** | A cookie that is inaccessible to client-side JavaScript, used to store JWT tokens securely. |\n226: | **Access Token** | A short-lived JWT (1 hour) that authorizes API requests. |\n227: | **Refresh Token** | A longer-lived JWT (7 days) used to obtain new access tokens without re-authentication. |\n228: | **RBAC** | Role-Based Access Control — restricts system access based on user roles (Renter, Admin). |\n229: | **JwtAuthGuard** | A NestJS guard that validates JWT from httpOnly cookies on protected routes. |\n230: | **RolesGuard** | A NestJS guard that checks user role permissions for accessing specific endpoints. |\n231: | **BaseController** | A base class providing automatic CRUD endpoints for controllers that extend it. |\n232: | **BaseService** | A base class providing automatic CRUD business logic for services that extend it. |\n233: | **BaseRepository** | A base class providing automatic TypeORM CRUD operations for repositories that extend it. |\n234: | **BaseEntity** | A base class providing UUID primary key, timestamps (`createdAt`, `updatedAt`), and soft delete (`deletedAt`) for all entities. |\n235: | **createAsyncThunk** | Redux Toolkit utility for creating async thunk actions for API calls in the frontend. |\n236: | **React Router 7 (Framework Mode)** | The routing system used by the frontend, where routes are defined declaratively using `route()`, `layout()`, and `index()` from `@react-router/dev/routes`. |\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ## Architecture Overview\n241: \n242: ### Backend: Four-Layer Architecture\n243: \n244: ```\n245: HTTP Request\n246:     ↓\n247: Controller  (extends BaseController)  — HTTP handling, validation, Swagger docs\n248:     ↓\n249: Service     (extends BaseService)     — Business logic, rules enforcement\n250:     ↓\n251: Repository  (extends BaseRepository)  — Data access, TypeORM queries\n252:     ↓\n253: Entity      (extends BaseEntity)      — Database schema (UUID PK, timestamps, soft delete)\n254:     ↓\n255: PostgreSQL + TypeORM\n256: ```\n257: \n258: ### Frontend Architecture\n259: \n260: - **Routing**: React Router 7 framework mode with `routes.ts` defining `route()`, `layout()`, `index()` patterns\n261: - **State Management**: Redux Toolkit with `createAsyncThunk` for API data fetching; Redux slices per domain feature\n262: - **Forms**: React Hook Form + Zod validation following shadcn/ui patterns\n263: - **Auth**: JWT httpOnly cookies with AuthContext, GuestGuard, and AuthGuard components\n264: - **Source Directory**: `app/` (not `src/`), imports use `~/` alias\n265: - **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4 + Shadcn/UI component library\n266: \n267: ### Directory Structure\n268: \n269: ```\n270: nestfind/\n271: ├── backend/\n272: │   ├── src/\n273: │   │   ├── core/              # Base classes, guards, decorators, filters\n274: │   │   │   ├── base/          # BaseEntity, BaseRepository, BaseService, BaseController\n275: │   │   │   ├── decorators/    # @Public(), @Roles(), @CurrentUser()\n276: │   │   │   ├── guards/        # JwtAuthGuard, RolesGuard\n277: │   │   │   ├── filters/       # HttpExceptionFilter\n278: │   │   │   ├── interceptors/  # TransformInterceptor, LoggingInterceptor\n279: │   │   │   └── pipes/         # ValidationPipe\n280: │   │   ├── modules/           # Feature modules (entity, repo, service, controller, module)\n281: │   │   ├── infrastructure/    # External services (mail, s3, token)\n282: │   │   └── database/          # Migrations, seeds\n283: │   └── test/                  # E2E tests\n284: ├── frontend/\n285: │   └── app/                   # Source directory\n286: │       ├── components/        # ui/, atoms/, modals/, shared/, layouts/, guards/\n287: │       ├── pages/             # Route pages\n288: │       ├── services/          # httpService.ts, httpMethods/, httpServices/\n289: │       ├── redux/             # features/, store/\n290: │       ├── types/             # .d.ts per domain\n291: │       ├── enums/             # Synced from backend\n292: │       ├── contexts/          # AuthContext\n293: │       ├── hooks/             # Custom hooks\n294: │       ├── lib/               # cn() utility\n295: │       ├── utils/             # errorHandler, validations/\n296: │       └── styles/            # Tailwind + theme variables\n297: └── docker-compose.yml\n298: ```\n299: \n300: ### API Base URLs\n301: \n302: | Environment | URL |\n303: |-------------|-----|\n304: | Development | `http://localhost:3000/api` |\n305: | Staging | `https://staging.nestfind.com/api` |\n306: | Production | `https://api.nestfind.com/api` |\n307: \n308: ---\n309: \n310: ## Related Documentation\n311: \n312: - [API Documentation](PROJECT_API.md) — Complete API endpoint specifications\n313: - [Database Schema](PROJECT_DATABASE.md) — Entity definitions and relationships\n314: - [API Integration](PROJECT_API_INTEGRATION.md) — Frontend-backend integration mapping\n315: - [Backend API Status](../status/backend/API_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md) — Backend implementation tracking\n316: - [Frontend Screen Status](../status/frontend/SCREEN_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md) — Frontend implementation tracking\n317: - [Architecture Decisions](../memory/DECISIONS.md) — Key technical decisions log\n318: - [Coding Patterns](../memory/LEARNINGS.md) — Patterns and insights\n319: \n320: ---\n321: \n322: *Generated: 2026-05-19 | Source: seed.yaml + architecture guides*\n\n(End of file - total 322 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE\n\n## Overview\n\n### Application Purpose\n\nNestFind is a streamlined rental property listing platform that connects renters with available properties. The platform focuses exclusively on rentals, providing a clean and efficient browsing experience where renters can search, filter, view details, save favorites, and submit inquiries to property managers. An accompanying admin dashboard enables administrators to manage property listings, respond to inquiries, and oversee user accounts.\n\nThe platform targets two primary user groups: Renters who browse and discover rental properties, and Administrators who manage the listings and respond to renter inquiries. NestFind integrates with Google Maps for property location display.\n\n### Technology Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|------------|\n| Backend | NestJS 11, TypeScript 5.7+ |\n| Frontend | React 19 with React Router 7 (framework mode) |\n| Database | PostgreSQL 16 |\n| ORM | TypeORM 0.3.x |\n| Authentication | JWT via httpOnly cookies (Access: 1h, Refresh: 7d) |\n| API Documentation | Swagger/OpenAPI |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md","time":{"start":1779182194007,"end":1779182194293}},"id":"prt_e3f85c78e001DXwvLXMoHHObNk","sessionID":"ses_1c07a6546ffe7dcCAj21iQXRj5","messageID":"msg_e3f859ee90010HYUJhmLTYQAau"}}
